<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Task Manager</title>
    <style>
        body{
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background:#f4f6f9;
            margin:0;
            padding:0;
            text-align:center;
        }

        header{
            background:#2c3e50;
            color:white;
            padding:25px;
        }

        main{
            margin-top:40px;
        }

        .container{
            width:60%;
            margin:auto;
        }

        .card{
            background:white;
            padding:20px;
            margin:20px;
            border-radius:10px;
            box-shadow:0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        a{
            display:inline-block;
            padding:12px 20px;
            margin:10px;
            background:#3498db;
            color:white;
            text-decoration:none;
            border-radius:6px;
        }

        a:hover{
            background:#2980b9;
        }

        footer{
            margin-top:40px;
            padding:15px;
            background:#ecf0f1;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

<header>
    <h1>Task Manager API</h1>
    <p>Backend Lab Project</p>
</header>

<main>
<div class="container">

<div class="card">
<h2>Navigation</h2>

<a href="/tasks">View All Tasks</a>
<a href="/tasks/new">Create New Task</a>
<a href="/friday">Friday Page</a>

</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>About</h3>
<p>
This project demonstrates a backend system built with Express, EJS templates,
and CRUD operations for task management.
</p>
</div>

</div>
</main>

<footer>
<p>Backend Lab Project – Node.js + Express + EJS</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>












